(firstQuint)Medical Need of OAC Reversal.

 This is a retrospective, observational, claims cohort study to assess, for adult patients initiating an oral anticoagulant for NVAF, the incidence rates of emergency surgery, major bleeding due to trauma, and major bleeding due to fracture, overall and stratified by age (75).

 The secondary objective is to estimate the overall and age stratified incidence of cardiac tamponade and peri-cardiocentesis.

